  "name": "RPlog_Hunter_Becomes_Corrupter",
  "title": "Confrontation at the Caspar Starport",
  "summary": "Having slipped out of the NR embassy to search the Caspar starport for Markus Lisardis's ship, the eccentric young woman Mira is shadowed protectively by Simon, who senses a dangerous presence. That presence is Kacela, a dark Force-wielding huntress who tied herself to Simon's destiny on Corellia and now grips Mira's shoulder, taunting Simon to come away with her. Simon confronts Kacela, accusing her of abducting Markus and Bazil, while she corrupts the mind of the bystander privateer Troy McTavish and conjures a small fireball that she hurls at Mira after the girl pelts her with a thrown rock. Simon deflects the flame with a flung wrench using the True Source, and the two trade strained threats and a searing psychic attack rather than open battle, both unwilling to spark a massacre in the crowded port. Kacela finally retreats into the shadows, vowing they will meet again, while Simon recovers and turns to check that Mira is unhurt as the curious onlooker Colin slips aboard the Conchobor to grab his supplies.",
